# duti config — set the preferred editor as default for code files.
# `__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__` is substituted by scripts/setup-user.sh with the
# detected editor (Antigravity preferred, Cursor fallback). Format:
#   <bundle-id>  <extension>  <role>
#
# Only list extensions here that resolve to STATIC UTIs on macOS. Extensions
# that resolve to dynamic UTIs (`dyn.*`) — e.g. .tsx, .toml, .scss, .fish —
# cause duti to fail with `error -50` because LaunchServices won't accept a
# dynamic UTI as a handler target. Those live in duti/extensions-by-tag and
# are applied via scripts/bind-extensions.sh.

# JavaScript / TypeScript
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .js    all

# Web — .html/.htm use `editor` role so the browser default (Chrome) is left
# alone; `all` would prompt the user to switch their default web browser.
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .html  editor
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .htm   editor
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .css   all

# Data / Config
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .json  all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .yaml  all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .yml   all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .xml   all

# General languages
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .py    all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .rb    all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .java  all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .php   all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .c     all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .cpp   all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .h     all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .hpp   all

# Shell / scripting
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .sh    all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .bash  all

# Docs / markup
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .md    all
__EDITOR_BUNDLE_ID__  .txt   all

# Note: Makefile and Dockerfile have no extension — set manually:
#   duti -s <bundle-id> public.unix-executable all
# Note: .swift, .xcodeproj, .xcworkspace intentionally excluded (stay with Xcode)
